    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-22T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-22T11:00:00-05:00" n="209"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d209">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.6363/486: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-22T13:00:00-03:00"
                            >November 22, 1941—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 22—11:46 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>490. In a note dated November 18 and received this morning<note n="15"
                        xml:id="d209fn1">Not printed.</note> the Foreign Office states that Uruguay
                    has decided to adhere to the oil pool. It reserves its decision as respects the
                    coordination of domestic distribution and requests information from the Embassy
                    regarding this phase of the matter. I am in some doubt as to just what the
                    appropriate Uruguayan authorities have in mind and shall discuss the matter with
                    Guani. I have already urged and shall continue to urge the prompt constitution
                    of the national pool committee. Text of code [<hi rend="italic">note?</hi>] and
                    full report by air mail.<note n="15" xml:id="d209fn2">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
